%N A211988 The Berndt-type sequence number 9 for the argument 2*Pi/13.
%C A211988 a(n) + A218655(n)*sqrt(13) = A(2*n+1)*13^((1+floor(n/3))/2)*sqrt(2*(13 + 3*sqrt(13))/13), where A(n) is defined below.
%C A211988 The sequence A(n) from the name of a(n) is defined by the relation A(n) = s(1)^(-n) + s(3)^(-n) + s(9)^(-n), where s(j) := 2*sin(2*Pi*j/13). The sequence with respective positive powers is discussed in A216508 (see sequence Y(n) in Comments to A216508).
%C A211988 It follows that A(n) = sqrt((13-3*sqrt(13))/2)*A(n-1) + (sqrt(13)-3)*A(n-2)/2 - sqrt((13-3*sqrt(13))/26)*A(n-3), with A(-1) = sqrt((13-3*sqrt(13))/2), A(0)=3, and A(1) = sqrt((13-3*sqrt(13))/2).
%C A211988 We note that s(1) + s(3) + s(9) = s(1)^(-1) + s(3)^(-1) + s(9)^(-1) = sqrt((13-3*sqrt(13))/2), sqrt(2*sqrt(13))*(s(1)^(-3) + s(3)^(-3) + s(9)^(-3)) = sqrt(97*sqrt(13)-339), and s(1)^(-9) + s(3)^(-9) + s(9)^(-9) = (131/13)*sqrt(2834 - 786*sqrt(13)).
%C A211988 The numbers of other Berndt-type sequences for the argument 2*Pi/13 in crossrefs are given.
